https://github.com/broadinstitute/gatk/blob/e8c49f600b06c658e0fa9bf67256340ebb46bc48/src/main/java/org/broadinstitute/hellbender/tools/spark/sv/utils/SVUtils.java#L283

At line 283, there is a Bitwise OR of a signed byte value with a long value.  As the code as is, the byte will get signed extended before the OR is performed.  If the byte value is negative, there will be bit 1’s extended in the OR .

The correct way is to first do a bitwise AND with 0xFF to zero out the extended 1’s.

val = (val <<8) | (toHash[i+j] & 0xFF);

Here is a code example that I think shows this:

		byte[] toHash = {(byte)0xF0,(byte)0xF1,(byte)0xF2,(byte)0xF3};

		// incorrect way, as done in line 283 in SVUtils.java
		long  val = 0;
		for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
			val = (val <<8) | toHash[i];      // incorrect way
		}		
		System.out.println("incorrect way:   val is     " + String.format("0x%08X", val));


		// correct way
		val = 0;
		for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
			val = (val <<8) | (toHash[i] & 0xFF);      // correct way
		}		
		System.out.println(" correct way:  val is     " + String.format("0x%08X", val));


The output of the above code snippet is:

incorrect way:   val is     0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF3
correct way:  val is     0xF0F1F2F3

I have been able to download files from the resource bucket successfully in the past but am now getting an access denied message. The same issue has also been reported in the [comments of the resource bundle article](https://gatk.broadinstitute.org/hc/en-us/articles/360035890811/comments/46046240434715) and [the community forum](https://gatk.broadinstitute.org/hc/en-us/community/posts/45984602007835-Access-denied-to-cloud-resource-bundle?brand_id=360002999131) by others  - the screenshot below is copied from the community forum, and is the same as what I see

